00:00:57.934 --> 00:01:00.674
Let me start with a simple statement.

00:01:01.544 --> 00:01:06.334
If you meet a person on the street and their only words to you

00:01:06.474 --> 00:01:11.734
are “I am lying, I am not telling the truth”, what do you think?

00:01:13.254 --> 00:01:20.014
Well, you probably think it’s a slightly odd thing for a stranger to say, but when you dig a

00:01:20.014 --> 00:01:26.844
little deeper and you really think about it, you realise that it is a problematic statement.

00:01:27.844 --> 00:01:33.254
If someone says “I am not telling the truth”, then their statement is

00:01:33.254 --> 00:01:37.764
both true and false, they are both telling the truth and they are lying.

00:01:38.774 --> 00:01:42.004
If their statement is true, that they are not telling

00:01:42.004 --> 00:01:45.264
the truth, then they are also telling the truth.

00:01:46.264 --> 00:01:51.954
Similarly, if their statement is false, and they are lying about not telling

00:01:51.954 --> 00:01:56.234
