00:02:24.814 --> 00:02:29.354
And this is the crux, the most important part, of a paradox.

00:02:29.874 --> 00:02:36.244
You can use logic and theory to prove that something is the case, even if we know that it is not.

00:02:37.984 --> 00:02:42.114
The grandfather of the paradox, even though he wasn't behind

00:02:42.124 --> 00:02:46.374
The Liar's Paradox, was a man called Zeno, Zeno of Elea.

